<html><body><p>See <a href="http://www.emacswiki.org/emacs/WindMove">http://www.emacswiki.org/emacs/WindMove</a> for details. </p> <p> My hotkeys are different from emacswiki because: </p><ul> <li>I was a vi guy, I prefer H,J,K,L for navigation. </li> <li>Arrow keys does not work on my terminal simulators.  <p>   Here is my hotkeys: </p></li> </ul>     


<pre class="prettyprint ">

(when (fboundp 'windmove-left)
  (global-set-key "\C-ch" 'windmove-left)
  (global-set-key "\C-cj" 'windmove-down)
  (global-set-key "\C-ck" 'windmove-up)
  (global-set-key "\C-cl" 'windmove-right))
</pre>


   <p> Note:   `C-c j` is originall hokey of function `join-line`. </p></body></html>